```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Integer = 3)
    if isa(dt, Date)
        error("Cannot increase date by timezone offset; use a Time type instead.")
    end
    return dt + Hour(bump * Dates.Hour)
end
```

This function `timezone_bumper` accepts a `DateTime` object and an optional integer `bump` specifying the number of hours to add (default is 3 hours). It returns a new `DateTime` with the original date plus the time zone offset applied. If no time zone offset is provided, it adds the default bump of 3 hours. The function ensures that the input type is `DateTime` and throws an error if someone tries to increase just the date without specifying a Time type.
